TITLE:Introducing BAX - Static Site Generator for Modern Web
DATE:15 July 2026
IMG:https://placehold.co/800x400/0f172a/ffffff?text=BAX+SSG
DESC:Learn about BAX, a lightweight and SEO-friendly static site generator built with pure Batch and Bash scripts. Zero dependencies, pure performance.
TAGS:bax static-site-generator ssg batch bash

H2:What is BAX?
P:BAX is a modern, lightweight, and SEO-friendly static site generator built with pure Batch (Windows) and Bash (Linux/Mac) scripts. No dependencies, no npm, no Python, no Ruby - just pure shell commands that transform simple .zet files into complete HTML websites.

P:BAX stands for "Batch and Axcora X" - combining the power of Windows Batch and Linux Bash with Axcora Tech's commitment to simplicity and performance.

H2:Why BAX?
P:BAX was created to solve a simple problem: static site generators are too complex. Most require installing large frameworks, learning complex templating languages, or managing dependencies.

H3:Key Benefits
UL:
LI:Zero Dependencies - No Node.js, npm, Python, Ruby, or Go required
LI:Cross-platform - Works on Windows, Linux, and macOS
LI:SEO Optimized - Auto-generates meta tags, Open Graph, and sitemaps
LI:Simple .zet Format - Easier than Markdown, more intuitive
LI:Lightning Fast - Builds in milliseconds, not seconds
LI:Zero Configuration - Most sites work with minimal setup
LI:Portable - Just copy the folder and run
LI:Open Source - MIT License, free forever
/UL:

H2:How to Use BAX
P:Getting started with BAX is incredibly simple:

H3:Step 1 - Clone
CODE:git clone https://github.com/mesinkasir/bax.git
CODE:cd bax

H3:Step 2 - Configure
P:Edit config.zet with your site information:

CODE:SITE_TITLE:My Awesome Site
CODE:SITE_URL:https://myawesome.site
CODE:SITE_DESCRIPTION:My awesome static site
CODE:POSTS_PER_PAGE:6

H3:Step 3 - Create Content
P:Add .zet files to the data/ folder:

CODE:TITLE:My First Blog Post
CODE:DATE:15 July 2026
CODE:IMG:https://example.com/image.jpg
CODE:DESC:This is my first post
CODE:TAGS:technology programming
CODE:
CODE:H2:Welcome!
CODE:P:Hello world! This is my first post.

H3:Step 4 - Build
P:Run the build command for your operating system:

CODE:bax.bat  # Windows
CODE:./bax.sh # Linux/Mac

H3:Step 5 - Deploy
P:Upload the public/ folder to your hosting provider:

UL:
LI:GitHub Pages
LI:Netlify
LI:Vercel
LI:Cloudflare Pages
LI:Any web hosting
/UL:

HR:

H2:BAX Features Deep Dive

H3:SEO Built-in
P:BAX automatically generates:
UL:
LI:Meta title and description tags
LI:Open Graph tags (Facebook, LinkedIn)
LI:Twitter Card tags
LI:Sitemap.xml
LI:Robots.txt
/UL:

H3:Simple Content Format
P:The .zet format is designed for humans, not machines:

CODE:TITLE:My Post
CODE:H2:Introduction
CODE:P:Simple content
CODE:UL:
CODE:LI:List item
CODE:/UL:

H3:Tag Support
P:BAX auto-generates tag pages for better organization and SEO.

H3:Pagination
P:BAX automatically paginates your blog posts with clean URLs.

H3:Responsive Design
P:BAX uses Bootstrap 5 for beautiful, responsive design out of the box.

HR:

